  "decision_conditions": [
    "INFORMATIVE: The applicant is advised that a rear roof extension constituting permitted development will be required to comply with the following restrictions and requirements imposed under Sub-sections B.1(a), B.2(a) and B.2(b)  of the 1995 Order as amended: \r\n\r\nSub-section B.1(a) -  No part of the works shall result in any part of the roof being higher than the highest point of the existing roof;\r\n\r\nSub-section B.2(a) - The materials used in any exterior work shall be of a similar appearance to those used in the construction of the exterior of the existing dwellinghouse;\r\n\r\nSub-section B.2(b) - Other than in the case of a hip-to-gable enlargement, the edge of the enlargement closest to the eaves of the original roof shall, so far as practicable, be not less than 20 centimetres from the eaves of the original roof."
